04:29.520 --> 04:30.810
A FAVOR. YEAH, I BET.

04:30.850 --> 04:31.980
[MAL] HEY, BOYS, BOYS.

04:32.020 --> 04:33.940
JAKE HAS ISSUES WITH SEEING
OTHER PEOPLE HAPPY.

04:33.980 --> 04:35.690
&lt;SIGHS&gt; YEAH, OKAY, SO I KNOW

04:35.730 --> 04:37.360
THERE'S A LITTLE BIT
OF A HISTORY THERE

04:37.400 --> 04:38.980
BETWEEN ME AND JESS,
THAT'S TRUE.

04:39.030 --> 04:41.320
A HISTORY? YEAH, YEAH.
IN YOUR FANTASY, LAD.

04:41.360 --> 04:42.900
HEY, WE HAD CHEMISTRY, OKAY?

04:43.530 --> 04:45.450
WALLY? LET'S GO.

04:49.540 --> 04:51.410
NICE SEEING YOU
AGAIN, JESSICA.

04:53.500 --> 04:54.710
SHE'S PLAYING HARD TO GET.

04:54.750 --> 04:55.880
JUST...

04:55.920 --> 04:57.380
LOOK, UH, FELLAS.

04:58.590 --> 04:59.710
I LIED.

04:59.750 --> 05:02.340
WE'RE A LITTLE DIVORCED.

05:02.970 --> 05:04.220
A LITTLE?

05:04.260 --> 05:06.010
I NEED TO GET MY WIFE BACK.

05:06.050 --> 05:09.060
I NEED YOUR HELP. I NEED...
I NEED TO SAVE MY LIFE.

05:12.350 --> 05:14.690
SO YOU TWO ARE GETTING
ALONG REALLY WELL, HEY?

05:14.730 --> 05:16.440
WELL, IT'S EASY BECAUSE
CHANDRA HAS SOME

05:16.480 --> 05:18.310
SERIOUSLY SUPER-HUMAN
QUALITIES.

05:18.360 --> 05:20.110
-DES, STOP IT.
-NO, NO, IT'S TRUE.

05:20.150 --> 05:21.440
SHE'S A BRILLIANT SWIMMER

05:21.480 --> 05:23.490
AND, UH, SHE HAS TO EAT
ALL OF HER FOOD...

05:23.530 --> 05:26.200
PROPORTIONATELY.
LIKE, LIKE, IN PROPORTION.

05:26.240 --> 05:27.450
&lt;COUGHING&gt;

05:29.030 --> 05:30.490
AND, LADIES, THAT'S WHY
I GARDEN,

05:30.540 --> 05:32.450
TO KEEP THE STRESS LEVELS
IN CHECK.

05:32.500 --> 05:33.330
RIGHT ON.

05:34.370 --> 05:36.540
UH, HOW ARE YOU, TINNY?

05:36.580 --> 05:37.880
HOW'S, UM, HIGH SCHOOL?

05:37.920 --> 05:40.420
JUST FINE.
THANK YOU FOR ASKING.

05:40.460 --> 05:41.550
THAT'S GREAT.

05:41.590 --> 05:42.920
YOU KNOW, I REMEMBER WHEN
I WAS IN HIGH SCHOOL.

05:42.960 --> 05:45.340
GOD, IT FEELS LIKE
SO LONG AGO.

05:45.380 --> 05:47.840
WHAT GRADE
ARE YOU IN AGAIN? 10?

05:47.890 --> 05:51.510
-12, ACTUALLY.
-OH, GOOD, GOOD.

05:51.560 --> 05:53.980
IT'S A SPECIAL YEAR.
I HOPE YOU ENJOY IT.

05:54.020 --> 05:56.100
MY GRADE 12 YEAR I JUST
HAD TO CRAM AND CRAM

05:56.140 --> 05:57.480
TO GET INTO PRE-MED, YOU KNOW?

05:57.810 --> 05:59.560
&lt;CHUCKLES&gt;

05:59.610 --> 06:01.820
WELL, ISN'T SHE ALL THAT
AND A BAG OF CHIPS?

06:01.860 --> 06:03.320
WELL, TINNY IS
AN AWESOME STUDENT.

06:03.360 --> 06:05.610
I MEAN, SHE GETS WICKED MARKS
WITHOUT EVEN STUDYING.

06:06.650 --> 06:08.240
OH. GOOD FOR HER.

06:10.030 --> 06:11.830
WHO'S THE EXTREME
SPORT ENTHUSIAST?

06:11.870 --> 06:13.580
OH, OURS. DES AND I.

06:13.620 --> 06:16.540
JUST A LITTLE FUN
WITH THE OLD SHUTTLECOCK.

06:16.580 --> 06:19.960
SO, OKAY, YEAH.
I'M GOING TO GO TO WORK NOW

06:20.000 --> 06:21.920
AND GO TO THE OFFICE.
WHY DON'T YOU
COME HELP ME, TINNY?

06:21.960 --> 06:23.590
NO, I'M GOOD ACTUALLY.

06:24.590 --> 06:25.590
WHY DON'T WE HAVE
A THREE-WAY?

06:26.720 --> 06:27.840
-WHAT?
-[DES] I... I MEAN,

06:27.880 --> 06:29.800
WITH BADMINTON,
BADMINTON, UH...

06:29.840 --> 06:31.470
DES? NO.

06:31.510 --> 06:33.810
NO? OKAY, OKAY,
I MEANT WITH
BADMINTON! I...

06:33.850 --> 06:35.350
I... ANYWAY,
I'M SORRY. NO?

06:35.390 --> 06:36.890
OKAY, I'M GOOD. OKAY.

06:39.980 --> 06:41.150
&lt;DOOR CLOSING&gt;

06:42.900 --> 06:44.610
BYE. FOR NOW.

06:47.400 --> 06:49.450
[JAKE] CLYDE, DO YOU WANT TO
TELL US WHAT THE HELL
WE'RE DOING HERE?

06:49.490 --> 06:51.370
YEAH, I JUST NEED TO
SEE THE BANK GUY.

06:51.410 --> 06:52.990
WELL, YOU TWO
ARE P.I.'S, RIGHT?

06:53.030 --> 06:55.620
SO, I'M HIRING YOU.

06:55.660 --> 06:56.620
YOU EVER HEAR OF A CHECK?

06:56.660 --> 06:58.660
LOOK, CLYDE, WE CAN
TALK ABOUT PAYMENT LATER.

06:58.710 --> 07:01.670
WE JUST NEED A LITTLE INFO
FROM YOU ABOUT WHAT IT IS YOU
THINK WE CAN DO TO HELP.

07:01.710 --> 07:04.130
AND, YOU KNOW, WHY MAYBE
YOU TRIED TO HANG YOURSELF.

07:04.170 --> 07:06.590
LOOK, I TOLD YOU
THAT WAS AN ACCIDENT.

07:06.630 --> 07:08.420
I JUST...

07:08.470 --> 07:10.590
I NEED TO TALK TO THIS GUY.
HE'S, HE...

07:10.640 --> 07:13.470
HE SORT OF FORECLOSED
ON MY HOUSE EARLIER THAN HE
SHOULD HAVE AND I, I...

07:13.510 --> 07:14.850
OH, OH, THERE HE IS!

07:14.890 --> 07:16.810
HEY, VALLIS!

07:17.270 --> 07:18.310
YEAH.

07:18.810 --> 07:20.020
GREAT TO SEE YOU AGAIN.

07:21.690 --> 07:24.270
CLYDE. CLYDE COWLEY.

07:25.690 --> 07:27.900
-HMM.
-YOU RIPPED OFF
MY HOUSE, REMEMBER?

07:29.200 --> 07:30.780
YOU... YOU...

07:30.820 --> 07:32.950
TRAITOROUS PIECE OF POO!

07:32.990 --> 07:34.700
CLYDE, JUST... JUST...

07:35.370 --> 07:36.410
HEY!

07:36.450 --> 07:38.120
STAY AWAY FROM ME.

07:38.160 --> 07:40.580
AND THIS BANK, OR YOU'LL END
UP IN JAIL, YOU HEAR ME?

07:42.670 --> 07:43.960
WHAT THE...

07:45.420 --> 07:46.670
[JAKE] UH...

07:48.050 --> 07:49.840
-CLYDE?
-[MAL] I THINK HE'S SNORING.

07:50.800 --> 07:51.800
&lt;CLYDE SNORING&gt;

07:55.760 --> 07:56.720
CLYDE.

07:58.470 --> 07:59.850
YOU FELL ASLEEP STANDING UP.

07:59.890 --> 08:02.770
I AM JUST EXHAUSTED.

08:02.810 --> 08:05.360
THAT'S A BAD SIGN. LET ME
GET MY EQUIPMENT. JUST...

08:06.520 --> 08:09.110
I THINK JEFF VALLIS,

08:09.150 --> 08:11.700
THE BANKER,
FORECLOSED ON MY HOUSE

08:11.740 --> 08:14.320
BECAUSE HE'S
SLEEPING WITH JESSICA.

08:14.370 --> 08:16.700
-DO YOU HAVE ANY PROOF?
-NO. BUT

08:16.740 --> 08:18.790
HE'S TRYING TO
MAKE ME LOOK LIKE A LOSER

08:18.830 --> 08:20.500
TO GET HER AWAY FROM ME.

08:20.540 --> 08:22.540
THAT'S WHY &lt;STUTTERS&gt;
I NEED TO

08:22.580 --> 08:24.710
GET THE HOUSE BACK,
FOR JESSICA.

08:24.750 --> 08:26.710
TO SHOW HER THAT I CAN.

08:26.750 --> 08:27.800
WHAT WOULD MAKE YOU THINK THAT

08:27.840 --> 08:29.550
JESSICA'S FOOLING AROUND
ON YOU WITH VALLIS?

08:29.590 --> 08:31.260
-YEAH.
-I DON'T KNOW.

08:31.300 --> 08:32.590
IT'S LIKE THE MINUTE WE
STARTED DEALING

08:32.630 --> 08:34.390
WITH THAT GUY FROM THE BANK

08:34.430 --> 08:36.010
SHE CHANGED. YOU KNOW?

08:36.050 --> 08:37.810
VALLIS SHOWS UP

08:37.850 --> 08:40.850
AND JESS WANTS ME SPENDING
MORE AND MORE.

08:40.890 --> 08:42.520
NOTHING'S GOOD ENOUGH
FOR HER.

08:42.560 --> 08:44.850
I KEPT REMORTGAGING THE HOUSE
JUST TO KEEP UP.

08:44.900 --> 08:46.690
AND THEN VALLIS FORECLOSES.

08:46.730 --> 08:48.520
I COULDN'T MAKE
THE PAYMENTS.

08:48.570 --> 08:50.530
BUT VALLIS, HE TOLD ME

08:50.570 --> 08:53.150
HE WOULD HOLD OFF,
BUT HE LIED TO ME.

08:53.200 --> 08:55.450
I FEEL LIKE THEY WERE BOTH
PLAYING ME, YOU KNOW, BECAUSE

08:55.490 --> 08:56.910
FIRST I LOSE THE HOUSE,

08:56.950 --> 08:58.870
AND THEN JESSICA,
SHE WANTS A DIVORCE.

09:00.080 --> 09:03.580
DAD AND I, OR I WILL,
WE'LL JUST GO TALK TO JESSICA.

09:03.620 --> 09:05.790
NO. NO, NO. DON'T DO THAT.
SHE'LL KNOW SOMETHING'S UP.

09:05.830 --> 09:07.630
I'M SURE SHE WILL.

09:07.670 --> 09:09.920
TRUST US. THIS IS OUR JOB.

09:14.050 --> 09:16.180
OKAY. SO,

09:16.220 --> 09:18.680
DROWSINESS IN
STRESSFUL SITUATIONS,

09:18.720 --> 09:20.220
UH, OVER-EXERTION,

09:20.260 --> 09:21.720
&lt;WHISPERS&gt; BED-WETTING,

09:21.770 --> 09:23.640
FEAR,
FIGHT-OR-FLIGHT INSTINCTS,

09:23.680 --> 09:26.730
FEAR OF THUMBTACKS, FLYING,
DRIVING, WALKING OR WATER,

09:26.770 --> 09:28.940
THOSE ARE ALL
SERIOUS, SERIOUS SYMPTOMS.

09:28.980 --> 09:30.940
I HAVE TO CATCH UP
WITH MALACHY.

09:30.980 --> 09:33.610
AH, AH, IT IS
IN MY HUMBLE OPINION

09:33.650 --> 09:35.110
THAT YOU HAVE
A MEDICAL CONDITION

09:35.150 --> 09:36.700
THAT YOU NEED TO SEE
A PHYSICIAN ABOUT.

09:36.740 --> 09:38.120
OR A MED STUDENT,
AND THAT CAN BE ARRANGED.

09:38.160 --> 09:39.330
WHAT ARE YOU TALKING ABOUT?

09:39.370 --> 09:41.240
YOU, SIR, ARE A TEXTBOOK

09:41.660 --> 09:42.700
NARCOLEPTIC.

09:42.750 --> 09:44.290
DON'T BE RIDICULOUS.

09:44.330 --> 09:45.920
HEY, NO. HEY, NO!

09:45.960 --> 09:47.790
YOU'RE IN NO CONDITION
TO DRIVE! GET A CAB!

09:47.830 --> 09:49.670
YOU'RE IN NO CONDITION... AH!

09:49.710 --> 09:51.380
[MAL] I KNOW HE WAS YOUR
ARCH ENEMY IN HIGH SCHOOL,

09:51.420 --> 09:54.170
BUT YOU REALLY HAVE TO
STOP ENJOYING CLYDE'S
SUFFERING SO MUCH.

09:54.220 --> 09:58.430
LOOK, OKAY? HE WAS A TERROR
TO EVERYONE, DAD, OKAY?

09:58.470 --> 10:00.180
HE PICKED ON WALTER EVERY
CHANCE THAT HE GOT.

10:00.220 --> 10:02.100
I CAN'T HELP
BUT THINK THAT THIS

10:02.140 --> 10:03.970
WHOLE THING, YOU KNOW,
IT MIGHT BE KARMA.

10:04.020 --> 10:05.100
YEAH, WELL, WATCH YOURSELF.

10:05.140 --> 10:06.770
THERE'S PLENTY OF KARMA
TO GO AROUND.

10:06.810 --> 10:08.690
-CLYDE'S LUXURY APARTMENT.
-&lt;JAKE LAUGHS&gt;

10:09.770 --> 10:11.940
HE ENDED UP LIVING IN HIS CAR.

10:11.980 --> 10:13.480
I GOTTA SAY, THAT'S PERFECT.

10:13.530 --> 10:14.690
THAT'S WHAT YOU CALL KARMA.

10:14.740 --> 10:16.450
STARTING TO SEE YOUR FUTURE?

10:16.490 --> 10:17.740
-&lt;LAUGHS&gt;
-VERY FUNNY.

10:17.780 --> 10:19.620
-SOMEONE LEAVING
NEWSPAPERS AROUND.
-&lt;DIRT BIKE REVVING&gt;

10:21.660 --> 10:22.950
THEY'RE ALL THE...

10:26.870 --> 10:28.580
SEE? KARMA.

10:29.210 --> 10:30.630
VERY FUNNY.

10:32.630 --> 10:33.710
WHAT IS THIS?

10:37.880 --> 10:39.840
JAKE AND MALACHY DOYLE.

10:39.890 --> 10:42.260
-WHO ARE YOU?
-AH.

10:42.300 --> 10:44.470
A MAN WHO DOESN'T
WASTE ANY TIME.

10:44.520 --> 10:45.680
I RESPECT THAT.

10:46.270 --> 10:48.850
YOUR, UH, CLIENT

10:48.890 --> 10:50.230
IS IN DEBT TO ME.

10:50.270 --> 10:52.230
WHAT ARE YOU TALKING ABOUT?
WHAT DEBT?

10:52.270 --> 10:53.980
IT'S A CONSIDERABLE AMOUNT.

10:54.020 --> 10:56.900
EVEN IN THIS PROVINCE'S
ROBUST ECONOMY.

10:56.940 --> 11:00.240
SO, DO I NOW LOOK TO YOU
FOR COMPENSATION?

11:00.820 --> 11:03.700
US? UH, NO, BOY.

11:03.740 --> 11:05.160
-HOW MUCH?
-&lt;TIRES SCREECHING&gt;

11:06.370 --> 11:08.040
YOU ASK CLYDE HOW MUCH.

11:10.880 --> 11:12.880
WHO WAS PONY TAIL BUDDY?

11:12.920 --> 11:15.670
NO IDEA, BUT I THINK
WE'D BETTER FIND OUT.

11:15.710 --> 11:17.380
JUST PUT IT ON
JAKE DOYLE'S TAB.

11:17.880 --> 11:19.180
[CHILI] HEY, DEADBEAT.

11:19.800 --> 11:21.090
I WANT TO TALK TO YOU.

11:21.140 --> 11:22.800
I'LL GET IT
BACK TO YOU, I PROMISE.

11:22.850 --> 11:25.970
YOU BET YOU WILL.
SO AS YOU DON'T FORGET...

11:26.020 --> 11:28.230
HEY, WHOA, WHOA, WHAT DO
YOU THINK YOU'RE DOING HERE?

11:29.480 --> 11:31.690
DON'T WORRY. MESSAGE SENT.

11:33.770 --> 11:36.320
CLYDE, YOU WANT TO TELL US
WHAT YOU GOT ON THE GO
WITH THIS GUY?

11:36.360 --> 11:38.150
HE THINKS I ROBBED HIM
OR SOMETHING. I DON'T KNOW.

11:38.190 --> 11:39.900
YEAH, RIGHT. OF COURSE.

11:39.950 --> 11:41.280
[JESSICA] WHAT IS GOING ON?

11:42.870 --> 11:44.580
ARE YOU STALKING ME?

11:44.620 --> 11:46.410
-HI, JESSICA.
-JESS, HONEY,

11:46.450 --> 11:48.870
-DON'T BE LIKE THAT NOW.
-DON'T CALL ME HONEY.

11:50.790 --> 11:51.870
THE BOYS ARE JUST
HELPING ME

11:51.920 --> 11:52.960
FINISH RENOING THE HOUSE,
YOU SEE?

11:53.000 --> 11:55.500
WE'RE GOING TO
KEEP IT PRETTY FOR YOU.

11:55.540 --> 11:57.800
CLYDE, WE DON'T OWN
THE HOUSE ANYMORE, REMEMBER?

11:57.840 --> 12:00.590
THE BANK FORECLOSED WHEN YOU
STOPPED PAYING THE MORTGAGE?

12:00.630 --> 12:02.800
I'M LUCKY THEY'RE
LETTING ME STAY UNTIL
THE END OF THE MONTH.

12:02.840 --> 12:04.470
UH, FAR BE IT
FOR ME TO INTERJECT,

12:04.510 --> 12:06.600
BUT DON'T YOU THINK MAYBE
THAT YOU MIGHT BE JUST...

12:06.640 --> 12:09.180
SLIGHTLY BEING
A LITTLE...
A LITTLE BIT HARD ON HIM?

12:09.230 --> 12:12.480
LOOK, CREEP,
I DON'T REMEMBER
YOU, OKAY? SO DROP IT.

12:12.520 --> 12:15.270
AND YOU,
DO I NEED A RESTRAINING ORDER?

12:15.310 --> 12:17.820
CLYDE, THE PAST IS JUST THAT.

12:17.860 --> 12:21.950
THE PAST. BEST YOU LEFT IT
BEHIND YOU AND MOVED ON.
I HAVE.

12:28.120 --> 12:30.750
[DES] OH, UH, THE NAME'S
CHILI POWER.

12:30.790 --> 12:32.830
-[JAKE] CHILI POWDER?
-POWER.

12:32.870 --> 12:34.170
HIS CHRISTIAN NAME'S LIAM.

12:34.210 --> 12:36.960
LIAM POWER.
HOW DO I KNOW THAT NAME?

12:37.000 --> 12:38.880
I THINK CLYDE'S A NARCOLEPTIC.

12:38.920 --> 12:41.720
-DES?
-SO, CHILI'S FROM AROUND
THE BAY ORIGINALLY,

12:41.760 --> 12:45.340
AND HE MADE SOME MAJOR MONEY
OUT IN FORT MAC
AND NOW HE'S HOME,

12:45.390 --> 12:46.800
AND HE'S LENDING IT OUT
ON THE STREET.

12:46.850 --> 12:48.720
SO, GUESSES ARE...

12:49.220 --> 12:50.890
CLYDE OWES HIM MONEY.

12:53.190 --> 12:55.400
MAN...

12:55.440 --> 12:59.070
OH, HOW DID I GET US
ROPED INTO HELPING THIS
SAD-SACK OF A FELLA?

12:59.110 --> 13:00.610
HE NEEDS OUR HELP,
AND YOU HAVE

13:00.650 --> 13:02.530
A NATURAL INCLINATION
TO HELP PEOPLE.

13:04.530 --> 13:05.820
I DON'T GET IT.
WHERE'S THE JOKE?

13:05.860 --> 13:07.660
THERE ISN'T ONE.
YOU'RE A GOOD BOY, JAKE.

13:07.700 --> 13:08.740
NOW...

13:10.200 --> 13:12.000
GO HELP
YOUR HIGH SCHOOL ENEMY.

13:14.000 --> 13:14.830
&lt;SIGHS&gt;

13:16.000 --> 13:17.630
[CLYDE] I DON'T KNOW,
I GUESS IT ALL

13:17.670 --> 13:19.420
JUST COMES DOWN TO
BAD LUCK, YOU KNOW?

13:19.460 --> 13:22.300
OR IT COULD BE THE FACT
THAT YOU'VE NEVER HAD TO
WORK FOR ANYTHING,

13:22.340 --> 13:25.760
AND YOU'VE BEEN
A DICK TO EVERYONE
FOR YOUR ENTIRE LIFE.

13:25.800 --> 13:29.560
ALL RIGHT. I WAS A JERK.
AT TIMES.

13:29.600 --> 13:31.520
BUT I WAS JUST BETTER
THAN EVERYONE ELSE.

13:31.560 --> 13:33.520
EVERYTHING I TOUCHED
TURNED TO GOLD.

13:33.560 --> 13:36.020
-YOU TRY LIVING WITH THAT.
-YEAH, IT MUST BE TOUGH

13:36.060 --> 13:37.020
LIVING IN YOUR OWN SHADOW.

13:37.060 --> 13:38.860
DO YOU REMEMBER
HOW GOOD I WAS AT BASEBALL?

13:38.900 --> 13:41.940
I WAS THE ONLY PLAYER
IN THIS PROVINCE TO
GET A BASEBALL SCHOLARSHIP.

13:42.440 --> 13:43.690
WHY DIDN'T YOU GO?

13:44.150 --> 13:45.740
JESS WANTED ME TO STAY.

13:46.820 --> 13:47.910
COULDN'T LIVE WITHOUT ME.

13:49.200 --> 13:51.410
NOW SHE DOESN'T EVEN
LOVE ME ANYMORE.

13:53.950 --> 13:55.540
HOW MUCH
DO YOU OWE CHILI?

13:57.120 --> 13:58.580
100 GRAND.

13:59.130 --> 14:00.290
PLUS THE JUICE.

14:01.670 --> 14:03.380
OH, GREAT.

14:03.420 --> 14:06.760
I JUST, I NEEDED A LITTLE BIT,
JUST TO GET BY, AND...

14:06.800 --> 14:08.680
&lt;CHUCKLES&gt; I LOST IT ALL.

14:08.720 --> 14:10.890
-POKER?
-NO, I LITERALLY LOST IT.

14:10.930 --> 14:13.890
IT WAS STOLEN, OR, OR,
OR LOST, OR WHATEVER.

14:13.930 --> 14:16.020
HOW DID YOU
MISPLACE $100,000?

14:16.060 --> 14:17.230
I...

14:18.560 --> 14:20.940
I GOT HOME AND I SAW
JESSICA WITH ANOTHER MAN.

14:22.020 --> 14:24.190
VALLIS. I'M SURE IT WAS HIM.

14:24.230 --> 14:25.950
I GOT NERVOUS AND...

14:26.860 --> 14:28.450
HAD AN EPISODE.

14:28.490 --> 14:31.160
I GET SLEEPY
WHENEVER I'M NERVOUS, OR

14:31.200 --> 14:33.790
EXCITED, OR ANGRY, OR UPSET.

14:33.830 --> 14:35.040
DES WAS RIGHT.
YOU'RE A NARCOLEPTIC.

14:35.080 --> 14:38.420
WHATEVER. I FELL ASLEEP,
PASSED OUT ON THE LAWN,

14:38.460 --> 14:40.420
WOKE UP
AND THE MONEY WAS GONE.

14:40.460 --> 14:44.050
I THINK THAT JESSICA
HAS MY MONEY AND SHE'S
HIDING IT IN THE HOUSE.

14:44.090 --> 14:46.670
ALL RIGHT, LET'S GO TO
YOUR HOUSE AND WE'LL
GET IT BACK, OKAY?

14:46.720 --> 14:47.800
REALLY?

14:49.010 --> 14:50.090
YOU'D DO THAT FOR ME?

14:51.180 --> 14:52.510
I'M ACTUALLY
DOING IT FOR MYSELF,

14:52.550 --> 14:54.220
BECAUSE I, I JUST REALLY...

14:54.260 --> 14:56.390
I DON'T WANT TO
DEAL WITH YOU ANYMORE.

14:58.730 --> 15:01.230
[CLYDE] VALLIS RUINED MY LIFE.

15:01.270 --> 15:03.940
OH, YEAH, VALLIS IS
THE PROBLEM HERE. SURE.

15:03.980 --> 15:06.030
FROM THE MINUTE WE MET HIM...

15:06.070 --> 15:07.490
VALLIS!

15:07.990 --> 15:10.240
FANCY SUITS AND WORDS.

15:10.820 --> 15:12.240
VALLIS.

15:12.280 --> 15:14.700
HE'S THE ONE THAT TOLD ME
TO REMORTGAGE THE HOUSE,

15:14.740 --> 15:16.330
HE FORECLOSES ON ME!

15:16.370 --> 15:19.040
ARE YOU EVEN LOOKING FOR
THE MONEY HERE, OR...

15:19.080 --> 15:21.130
JUST GOTTA MAKE SURE
THERE'S NO NEW
MAN-STUFF HERE.

15:21.170 --> 15:23.380
CLYDE, FOCUS, OKAY?

15:23.420 --> 15:26.090
WHERE WOULD YOUR WIFE
HIDE $100,000?

15:27.300 --> 15:28.510
THE SAFE.

15:35.810 --> 15:38.060
DAMN IT. IT'S EMPTY.

15:38.100 --> 15:39.980
NICE. YOU KNOW,
I'M STARTING TO THINK

15:40.020 --> 15:42.810
THAT THERE WAS NO
$100,000 IN THE FIRST PLACE.

15:44.060 --> 15:45.110
&lt;JESSICA LAUGHING&gt;

15:45.150 --> 15:47.530
OH! OH! IF SHE FINDS ME HERE
SHE'LL FREAK. SHE'LL DO IT.

15:47.570 --> 15:49.280
SHE'LL FREAK!
SHE'LL TOTALLY FREAK!

15:49.320 --> 15:51.780
CALM DOWN, CALM DOWN!
JUST GET IN THERE.

15:57.330 --> 15:59.750
MAKE YOURSELF AT HOME.

15:59.790 --> 16:02.420
-I'LL JUST BE A SEC.
-SHE'S WITH VALLIS.
I TOLD YOU.

16:04.920 --> 16:06.170
DON'T YOU LOOK AT HER...

16:07.210 --> 16:08.630
&lt;SNORING&gt;

16:22.140 --> 16:23.810
HEY, ARE WE HAVING
A DRINK OR WHAT?

16:24.440 --> 16:26.230
WALLY!

16:26.270 --> 16:27.980
YOU ALMOST CAUGHT ME NAKED.

16:28.030 --> 16:30.990
OH, SORRY.
DO YOU WANT ME TO RE-ENTER
AND TRY THAT AGAIN?

16:31.740 --> 16:33.200
YOU DEVIL.

16:38.290 --> 16:39.700
YOU SON OF A...

16:46.210 --> 16:47.670
I'M GOING TO GET US SOME WINE.

16:53.300 --> 16:54.470
YES.

16:58.970 --> 17:00.430
WHAT THE HELL ARE YOU DOING?

17:00.470 --> 17:02.770
WHAT AM I DOING? YOU'RE THE
ONE HIDING IN HER CLOSET!

17:02.810 --> 17:04.690
SHE IS MARRIED,
WALTER. MARRIED!

17:04.730 --> 17:06.110
ARE YOU SPYING
ON ME OR SOMETHING?

17:06.150 --> 17:08.480
HAVE YOU NO RESPECT FOR
THE SANCTITY OF MARRIAGE?

17:08.520 --> 17:09.900
THIS WOULD KILL CLYDE.

17:10.820 --> 17:11.990
&lt;WALTER GASPS&gt;

17:12.030 --> 17:13.360
IS, IS THAT CLYDE?

17:13.400 --> 17:16.120
-IS HE DEAD?
-YES, AND, NO.

17:16.160 --> 17:18.580
[JESSICA] WALLY,
IS WHITE OKAY?

17:18.620 --> 17:20.080
THE RED'S
DOWN IN THE BASEMENT.

17:20.120 --> 17:23.410
UH, NO. UH. NO.
NO, RED IS BEST.

17:23.460 --> 17:27.250
UH, WHITE, I GET ALL...
IT MAKES ME ALL, UH, VOMITY.

17:27.290 --> 17:30.670
[JESSICA] OKAY. I'LL GET
THE RED THEN.

17:30.710 --> 17:33.590
YOU'RE JUST JEALOUS
BECAUSE I GOT HER
AND YOU DIDN'T.

17:33.630 --> 17:35.590
WHATEVER, OKAY? JUST HELP
ME GET HIM OUT OF HERE.

17:35.630 --> 17:37.970
HE'S ASLEEP.
IT'S A LONG STORY.

17:40.060 --> 17:41.810
WHAT ARE YOU HELPING
HIM FOR ANYWAY?

17:41.850 --> 17:43.930
HE WAS SUCH A DICK-SMACK
TO US IN HIGH SCHOOL.

17:43.980 --> 17:45.100
OH! &lt;LAUGHS&gt;

17:45.140 --> 17:46.350
YOU REMEMBER THAT TIME

17:46.400 --> 17:47.600
THAT HE BEAT ME UP

17:47.650 --> 17:48.940
AND HE STOLE MY PANTS

17:48.980 --> 17:50.650
-AND MY UNDERWEAR?
-SHH!

17:50.690 --> 17:52.190
YOU WEREN'T
WEARING ANY UNDERWEAR.

17:52.230 --> 17:54.400
-LOOK, THAT'S NOT
THE POINT, OKAY?
-&lt;CELL PHONE RINGING&gt;

17:55.700 --> 17:57.160
[JESSICA] HEY, IS THAT MINE?

17:57.200 --> 18:00.450
UH, YEAH. YEAH. A LITTLE HELP
HERE PLEASE? COULD YOU...

18:04.370 --> 18:06.170
IT'S A TEXT. FROM VALLIS.

18:06.210 --> 18:08.130
-SHE'S MEETING HIM TOMORROW.
-SO?

18:08.670 --> 18:10.170
WHO? HELP!

18:11.210 --> 18:12.300
[JESSICA] WALLY?

18:14.170 --> 18:15.670
SHUT UP, CLYDE.

18:15.720 --> 18:17.510
-CLYDE, SHUT UP!
-&lt;GROANING&gt;

18:20.640 --> 18:21.810
-&lt;CRASH&gt;
-&lt;CAT YOWLS&gt;

18:21.850 --> 18:24.100
-GET OUT.
-THIS ISN'T OVER.

18:24.140 --> 18:25.100
&lt;SCREAMS&gt;

18:27.940 --> 18:29.310
YOU GOT A TEXT! &lt;PANTING&gt;

18:29.860 --> 18:31.480
THANKS.

18:31.520 --> 18:34.610
I, UH, HOPE IT
DOESN'T MAKE YOU VOMITY.

18:38.950 --> 18:42.530
[CLYDE] WAS SHE WITH VALLIS?
WAS IT HIM? I BET IT WAS HIM.

18:42.580 --> 18:46.330
-I KNOW IT WAS HIM!
-IT WASN'T HIM. IT WAS...

18:47.410 --> 18:48.830
IT WAS HER LAWYER,

18:48.870 --> 18:53.210
WHO, BY THE WAY, YOU TORTURED
EVERY DAY IN HIGH SCHOOL.

18:53.250 --> 18:55.960
WALTER? WALTER THE FALTER?

18:56.010 --> 18:57.800
NO WORRIES OF HER
STEPPING OUT WITH HIM.

18:57.840 --> 18:59.180
THE FATTY.

18:59.220 --> 19:00.430
YOU JUST WATCH
YOURSELF, CLYDE.

19:00.470 --> 19:01.600
WHY?

19:04.060 --> 19:05.310
WE GOING TO FIGHT AGAIN?

19:07.060 --> 19:09.730
-LIKE IN HIGH SCHOOL?
-WHOA, WHOA,
SETTLE DOWN, BOYS.

19:09.770 --> 19:11.230
I WOULDN'T
WORRY ABOUT IT, DAD.

19:11.270 --> 19:13.650
FOR CLYDE'S SAKE I DON'T THINK
THAT'S A GOOD IDEA, AND...

19:13.690 --> 19:14.980
WAIT A MINUTE!

19:15.030 --> 19:17.610
WHEN I PASSED OUT,
SHE WAS UNDRESSING.

19:17.650 --> 19:18.860
DID YOU SEE HER NAKED?

19:19.450 --> 19:20.860
DID YOU SEE HER NAKED?

19:21.990 --> 19:24.240
NO, BOY. SHE, UM...
&lt;CLEARS THROAT&gt;

19:25.410 --> 19:26.540
WENT TO THE BATHROOM.

19:28.660 --> 19:30.620
WE GOTTA FIGURE OUT
THIS SITUATION WITH CHILI.

19:30.670 --> 19:31.830
HE'S A DANGEROUS ONE.

19:31.880 --> 19:33.960
AH, DON'T WORRY ABOUT HIM.
I'LL DEAL WITH HIM.

19:34.000 --> 19:35.670
WE NEED TO DEAL WITH VALLIS.

19:35.710 --> 19:38.170
WHAT'S HIS, UH,
CONNECTION TO JESSICA?

19:38.220 --> 19:40.220
HE WANTS
INTO HER AWESOME PANTS.

19:40.260 --> 19:43.930
HE WORKS AS A LOAN OFFICER
AT THE BANK AND JESSICA

19:43.970 --> 19:46.310
HAS A MEETING WITH HIM AT
10:00 THIS MORNING.

19:46.350 --> 19:48.480
MAYBE SHE WANTS
TO RENEGOTIATE,
GET THE HOUSE BACK!

19:49.850 --> 19:51.350
IT'D BE GOOD TO HAVE
EARS ON THE INSIDE.

19:51.400 --> 19:53.400
YEAH.

19:53.440 --> 19:56.860
WE SHOULD SEND SOMEONE IN
UNDERCOVER, YOU KNOW,
TO PLANT A BUG.

19:56.900 --> 20:01.110
MAYBE, UH, TWO KIDS POSING
AS A YOUNG COUPLE LOOKING
TO BUY A NEW HOME?

20:05.950 --> 20:07.790
[JAKE] OKAY, THAT'S THE
LAPEL CAMERA, ALL RIGHT?

20:07.830 --> 20:10.250
PUT IT SOMEWHERE
WHERE WE CAN'T SEE IT, DES.
THAT'S THE IDEA.

20:10.290 --> 20:12.330
AND THIS IS A BUG, ALL RIGHT?
YOU NEED TO PLANT IT,

20:12.370 --> 20:14.840
BECAUSE I NEED TO HEAR
WHATEVER IS GOING ON IN
VALLIS' OFFICE

20:14.880 --> 20:17.840
AFTER YOU LEAVE. PUT IT ON HIS
DESK, BRIEFCASE, WHATEVER.

20:17.880 --> 20:19.760
OKAY, OKAY, BUT, BUT...
ME AND TINNY?

20:19.800 --> 20:21.430
I MEAN, REALLY?
DON'T YOU THINK
THAT'S KIND OF DANGEROUS?

20:21.470 --> 20:22.840
I MEAN, WE'RE NOT REALLY
IN A GOOD PLACE RIGHT NOW

20:22.880 --> 20:24.550
IF WE'RE LOOKING
FOR A HOUSE TOGETHER.

20:24.590 --> 20:27.220
TINNY'S IN THE BANK
WAITING FOR YOU RIGHT NOW.

20:27.260 --> 20:28.430
JUST WAIT.
DON'T GET MAD AT ME.

20:28.470 --> 20:30.180
I'VE BEEN WAITING TO
TALK TO YOU ABOUT THIS.

20:32.020 --> 20:33.190
I THINK TINNY HATES ME.

20:33.650 --> 20:35.150
OF COURSE SHE HATES YOU.

20:35.190 --> 20:37.610
SHE DOES? DID SHE SAY ANYTHING
TO YOU? DID SHE SAY ANYTHING?

20:41.280 --> 20:43.990
SO, I FIXED DES
WITH A LAPEL CAMERA

20:44.030 --> 20:46.450
AND IT SHOULD BE COMING
THROUGH RIGHT NOW.

20:48.580 --> 20:50.500
BANG UP JOB AGAIN.

20:50.540 --> 20:52.790
WILL WE BE FINDING OUT IF
JESS AND VALLIS ARE HAVING
AN AFFAIR NOW OR NOT?

20:52.830 --> 20:55.170
THEY'RE NOT, OKAY?
BUT WE THINK

20:55.210 --> 20:57.880
THAT JESS, YOUR WIFE,
IS STEALING YOUR MONEY.

20:57.920 --> 20:59.630
BUT IF YOUR WIFE WENT ON
A SPENDING SPREE

20:59.670 --> 21:00.880
JUST BEFORE
YOU LOST THE HOUSE...

21:00.920 --> 21:03.130
MAYBE SHE OWES VALLIS MONEY.

21:03.180 --> 21:05.510
-&lt;PHONE RINGING&gt;
-OR MAYBE VALLIS MADE HER
STEAL MY 100 G'S.

21:09.350 --> 21:12.270
-HELLO?
-WE NEED TO TALK RIGHT NOW.

21:12.310 --> 21:14.060
YEAH, NOW'S NOT
A VERY GOOD TIME.

21:15.560 --> 21:17.520
IT WAS... OH, HEY! LOOK.

21:17.560 --> 21:19.230
-[DES] ONE, TWO...
-WE'VE GOT SOUND.

21:19.270 --> 21:20.480
[DES] JAKE, CHECK.

21:21.780 --> 21:24.070
WOW, YOU LOOK AMAZING.

21:24.110 --> 21:27.280
I MEAN, YOU, YOU LOOK GREAT.
YOU, YOU, YOU LOOK NICE.

21:27.320 --> 21:29.700
JUST DRESSING THE PART.
DON'T FREAK OUT.

21:29.740 --> 21:32.410
OKAY, UM, ALL RIGHT
SO DO WE HAVE A PLAN?

21:32.450 --> 21:33.710
I MEAN, WHAT'S THE PLAN?
WE SHOULD HAVE A PLAN.

21:33.750 --> 21:35.250
WAS I SUPPOSED
TO HAVE THE PLAN?

21:35.290 --> 21:37.420
-DES...
-OH, YEAH. HOLD ON A SEC.

21:37.460 --> 21:39.500
MR. VALLIS, I'M SORRY WE
DON'T HAVE AN APPOINTMENT,

21:39.540 --> 21:41.420
BUT CAN WE JUST HAVE
A MINUTE OF YOUR TIME?

21:42.210 --> 21:43.340
CALL YOU BACK.

21:45.090 --> 21:46.970
I THINK IT'S THE RIGHT THING
FOR US TO BUY A HOUSE.

21:47.010 --> 21:48.140
DON'T YOU, HONEY?

21:49.510 --> 21:51.520
SO, UH, WHAT CAN I
DO FOR YOU KIDS?

21:51.560 --> 21:53.980
WELL, WE'RE NOT EXACTLY KIDS.
I'M IN MED SCHOOL,

21:54.020 --> 21:55.560
WHICH MAKES ME
A BIT OF A DICK,

21:55.600 --> 21:58.020
BUT WE'RE IN LOVE SO

21:58.060 --> 21:59.820
WE JUST WANT TO
START LOOKING AT HOUSES.

21:59.860 --> 22:00.980
THAT'S WHAT YOU
SPECIALIZE IN, RIGHT?

22:01.020 --> 22:02.400
HOUSES, MORTGAGES?

22:02.440 --> 22:05.200
WELL, FIRST THING'S FIRST.
ARE YOU HERE FOR PRE-APPROVAL

22:05.240 --> 22:06.910
OR DO YOU HAVE
A PROPERTY IN MIND?

22:06.950 --> 22:09.410
OH, I'VE GOT
A PROPERTY IN MIND.

22:09.450 --> 22:10.490
&lt;BREATHES HEAVILY&gt;

22:10.530 --> 22:12.870
DES, ARE YOU SURE
YOU WANT TO GET
ALL SETTLED IN

22:12.910 --> 22:14.080
WITH A MED STUDENT,

22:14.120 --> 22:16.460
BUY A HOUSE,
HAVE LITTLE
MED STUDENT BABIES?

22:16.500 --> 22:18.710
OH, MY GOD. OH, MY GOD.

22:18.750 --> 22:21.550
IS HE, UH, IS HE OKAY,
OR... YEAH?

22:21.590 --> 22:22.880
DOESN'T LOOK OKAY.

22:22.920 --> 22:24.510
OH.

22:24.550 --> 22:26.720
OH, MY GOD!
YOU KNOW WHAT? HE'S...

22:26.760 --> 22:28.550
HE'S ALLERGIC TO PAPER.

22:28.590 --> 22:30.600
I THINK HE'S GOING INTO
ANAPHYLACTIC SHOCK!

22:30.640 --> 22:31.430
OH, DEAR.

22:31.470 --> 22:32.970
WHAT IN GOD'S NAME
IS SHE DOING?

22:33.010 --> 22:35.100
OH, MY GOD. YOU'D BETTER
GO GET ONE OF THOSE ALLERGY

22:35.140 --> 22:38.600
NEEDLE PENS OR HE WILL
DIE RIGHT HERE.

22:38.650 --> 22:40.360
I'M FREAKING OUT. I'M SORRY
I'M FREAKING OUT,

22:40.400 --> 22:41.480
BUT WHY ARE YOU
FREAKING ME OUT?

22:41.520 --> 22:44.230
-DES, JUST RELAX.
-OKAY.

22:44.280 --> 22:46.400
WHOA, OH, MY GOD. OH, MY GOD.
WHAT DO YOU WANT FROM ME?

22:46.440 --> 22:48.320
THE BUG. YOU KNOW,
THE BUG WE'RE HERE TO PLANT?

22:48.360 --> 22:49.570
RIGHT, RIGHT, RIGHT. RIGHT,
RIGHT, RIGHT, RIGHT.

22:49.610 --> 22:51.870
THE BUG. OKAY.
OKAY, I GOT IT. I GOT...

22:52.950 --> 22:54.120
ALL RIGHT.

22:54.160 --> 22:55.950
-&lt;FEEDBACK&gt;
-&lt;SCREAMS&gt;

22:56.000 --> 22:58.080
-DON'T MOVE.
-OKAY.

22:59.040 --> 23:00.210
&lt;SCREAMING&gt;

23:01.840 --> 23:03.590
UH, STAB HIM THREE TIMES.

23:03.630 --> 23:05.170
-ARE YOU SURE?
-YEAH, I'M A MED STUDENT.

23:05.210 --> 23:06.880
-TRUST ME.
-&lt;SOBS&gt;

23:07.670 --> 23:08.430
&lt;SCREAMS&gt;

23:14.470 --> 23:16.810
-YOU KNOW WHAT? HE'S GOING TO
BE JUST FINE IF WE GET...
-&lt;PHONE RINGING&gt;

23:16.850 --> 23:19.230
WE'D BETTER GO
TO THE HOSPITAL. THANK YOU.

23:21.480 --> 23:22.610
UNCLE JAKE, WE GOT SOMETHING.

23:24.270 --> 23:25.360
[JAKE] WHAT IS ALL THIS STUFF?

23:25.400 --> 23:27.320
[MAL] LOOKS LIKE
JESSICA'S BANK RECORDS.

23:27.360 --> 23:29.320
HOW'S THAT GOING TO
HELP ME GET JESSICA BACK?

23:30.490 --> 23:32.530
-&lt;GROANS&gt;
-&lt;PEOPLE GASP&gt;

23:32.570 --> 23:34.370
ALL RIGHT, CLYDE, MY SON.

23:35.540 --> 23:37.080
NOW WE DO THIS MY WAY.

23:37.750 --> 23:39.120
DON'T MAKE ME USE IT.

23:40.580 --> 23:42.040
DON'T EVEN THINK OF IT.

23:42.420 --> 23:43.420
&lt;THUD&gt;

23:45.630 --> 23:46.760
&lt;CLYDE SNORING&gt;

23:54.760 --> 23:56.600
SHOULD WE GO AFTER HIM, OR...

23:59.180 --> 24:00.390
OW, THAT HURT.

24:02.690 --> 24:04.650
I MEAN, I FEEL FINE.
I MEAN, I FEEL FINE, LIKE...

24:04.690 --> 24:06.320
NOT IN LIKE A WICKED WAY,
BUT, OKAY, I JUST GOT,

24:06.360 --> 24:07.860
I JUST REALLY GOT
SOME LIKE, ENERGY.

24:07.900 --> 24:09.950
I MEAN, SHOULD I BE AT
THE HOSPITAL?
WE SHOULD CALL CHANDRA.

24:10.700 --> 24:12.660
